From Bill Mayhew Subject Re Laser vs Bubblejet FYI The actual horizontal dot placement resoution of an HP deskjet is The electronics and dynamics of the ink cartridge however limit you to generating dots at per On almost any paper the ink wicks more than inch The method of depositing and fusing toner of a laster printer results in much less spread than ink drop It doesn't take much investigation to see that the mechanical and electronic complement of a laser printer is more complex than inexpensive ink jet Recall also that laser printers offer a much higher throughput ppm for a laser versus about ppm for an ink jet Something else to think about is the cost of consumables over the life of the A page yield toner cartridge is about US at discount while HP high capacity page yield cartridges are about US at It could be that over the life cycle of the printer that consumables for laser printers are less than ink jet It is getting progressively closer between the two Laser printers are usually desinged for higher duty cycles in pages per month and longer product replacement Bill Mayhew NEOUCOM Computer Services Department Rootstown OH USA phone